attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, ARM, EABI4 version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, with debug_info, not stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a DDoS botnet agent, likely a variant of the Mirai or Gafgyt families, targeting ARM-based IoT devices. It features a comprehensive suite of DDoS attack vectors including TCP SYN/ACK floods, UDP floods, and VSE (Valve Source Engine) query floods. The sample includes a 'killer' module (killer_lol) that iterates through /proc to terminate competing malware and common administrative tools like wget and curl. It also employs process masquerading techniques (hide_process) by manipulating /proc/self/cmdline and symlinks. Relevant IOCs include the hardcoded C2/reporting IP 37.221.92.196 and its attempt to bind to port 4001 (0x0fa1) to ensure a single running instance.
